Formula Bharat is a premier engineering design competition where student teams design, build, and validate a Formula-style electric race car.
The competition evaluates teams across:
1.Engineering Design
2.Electrical & Mechanical Systems
3.Safety & Reliability
4.Cost & Manufacturing
5.Dynamic performance (on-track events)

Our goal was to develop a safe, efficient, and competition-compliant electric vehicle, focusing on robust electrical architecture and control systems.

I worked primarily on safety systems, PCB design, and system integration.
1. BSPD (Brake System Plausibility Device) – PCB Design
   Designed and implemented the BSPD circuit to ensure vehicle safety compliance.
      Developed PCB layout using EDA tools.
      Signal routing and grounding strategies
      Ensured the system detects: Simultaneous brake + throttle conditions
      Integrated shutdown logic to disable motor in unsafe scenarios
2. FMEA (Failure Mode and Effects Analysis)
   Contributed to preparation of FMEA documentation
      Identified:Potential electrical and system-level failures
      Their impact and severity
      Proposed mitigation strategies to improve:
      Reliability
      Safety compliance
3. Embedded & Control Integration
    Assisted in integrating:
     Sensors
     Motor control signals
     Safety feedback loops
   Ensured proper signal flow between:
     Motorcontroller(BAMOCAR)
     Motor(EMRAX208) 
     Safety systems
